The paper deals with deterministic parallel algorithms for combinatorial optimization problems, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of computer science such as data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), information theory (cs.IT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper's focus on randomized algorithms and their derandomization also suggests a connection to the sub-field of probabilistic algorithms (cs.PR). However, since the paper's main applications are in combinatorial optimization, we consider cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.DM, and cs.CG to be the most likely sub-categories.
